---
const chips = ["Epicor ERP / Kinetic", "CPQ & pricing logic", "ERP integrations & APIs", "Process automation", "SQL / dashboards", "GCP / Firebase"];
---
<section id="about" class="bp-light">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="head-row" style="margin-bottom:40px">
      <div style="max-width:42rem">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h2 class="display">A builder who's run the systems — not just advised on them.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about">
        <p class="lead">I'm Braeden Johnston, founder of Stockdale Systems. For years I was the one-person technical product team behind a manufacturer's enterprise systems — architecting a CPQ engine from scratch, launching a customer portal for 2,000+ users, and building the dashboards and automations that handed hundreds of hours back to operations.</p>
        <p>I started Stockdale Systems to do that work for more manufacturers: confront the brutal facts of your current systems honestly, then build the software, integrations, and automation that actually move the numbers — margin, revenue, and hours saved. You work directly with me, from first call to final hand-off.</p>
        <p style="font-size:.95rem">Background: a degree in Project Management with a minor in Global Supply Chain Management, deep Epicor (ERP / Kinetic) and CPQ experience, and full-stack, API, and cloud architecture.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="panel">
        <h3>Focus &amp; toolbox</h3>
        <div class="chips">
          {chips.map((c) => <span class="chip2">{c}</span>)}
        </div>
        <h3 style="margin-top:24px">Direct line</h3>
        <p class="mono" style="font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8">
          Issaquah, WA · serving manufacturers<br />
          <a href="mailto:contact@stockdalesystems.com" style="color:var(--teal)">contact@stockdalesystems.com</a><br />
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/braedenjohnston/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:var(--teal)">linkedin.com/in/braedenjohnston</a>
        </p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
